Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are energy conversion devices that can solve the energy crisis and environmental pollution, but the low electrochemical performance at intermediate temperatures is still an urgent problem to be addressed.
Titulo: Monovalent ion doping to enhance the performance of cobalt-free Sm0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ cathode for YSZ fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, we investigate the effect of K and F doping on the performance of conventional cobaltfree cathode SSF.
Titulo: Monovalent ion doping to enhance the performance of cobalt-free Sm0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ cathode for YSZ fuel cells

Sentencas: XRD demonstrates that SSF, SSKF, SSFF, and SSKFF each display a cubic perovskite structure.
Titulo: Monovalent ion doping to enhance the performance of cobalt-free Sm0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ cathode for YSZ fuel cells

Sentencas: Additionally, HT-XRD reveals that SSF, SSKF, and SSFF exhibit exceptional thermal stability, while SSKFF produces the impurity phase Sr3Fe2O7 during the test.
Titulo: Monovalent ion doping to enhance the performance of cobalt-free Sm0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ cathode for YSZ fuel cells

Sentencas: XPS suggests that the improvement in SSF performance, resulting from F and K doping, can be largely attributed to the increase in adsorbed oxygen content, which enhances the ORR catalytic activity.
Titulo: Monovalent ion doping to enhance the performance of cobalt-free Sm0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ cathode for YSZ fuel cells

Sentencas: The O-2-TPD outcomes indicate that F and K doping stimulate the formation of oxygen vacancies at higher temperatures, thus promoting ORR catalytic activity.
Titulo: Monovalent ion doping to enhance the performance of cobalt-free Sm0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ cathode for YSZ fuel cells

Sentencas: Experimentally, the electrochemical impedance spectra results indicate that both K and F doping led to a reduction in the value of polarization resistance, which decreased by over 20% at 800 degrees C. Regarding the output performance, both K and F doping resulted in a substantial increase in the output power from 670.05 to 825.88 and 796.76 mW center dot cm(-2) respectively, at 800 degrees C. However, co-doping with F and K led to a notable reduction in polarization impedance and output power, possibly due to the formation of heterogeneous phases during testing.
Titulo: Monovalent ion doping to enhance the performance of cobalt-free Sm0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ cathode for YSZ fuel cells

Sentencas: The results indicate that enhancing the electrochemical performance of SSF can be achieved through the doping of K cations and F anions, but co-doping leads to a decreased performance.
Titulo: Monovalent ion doping to enhance the performance of cobalt-free Sm0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ cathode for YSZ fuel cells
